content: Will not let me use the app

I had this app installed for a while, but when I opened my phone this morning, it said that the app was a virus. Never had this happen before but the flagged virus was a clicker Trojan. I'll just stick with the website unless this is fixed.
The last storm was very inaccurate and the app hasn't been working part of the time to even calculate anything.
Really helpful and pretty accurate
Paid and still doesn't show 3 days...no text alert either...was disappointed because it is usually pretty accurate
Very inaccurate
Very buggy, sometimes it doesn't work properly
Predicted snow days very accurately I loved the app it's not always accurate because it's all in the hands of the school
Works good on my note 9 100%
App is broken. Half the features don't work.
Really inaccurate
horrible crashes all the time

Don't pay for extra days! I paid to see the 3 extra days and for text alerts. I never see 3 days out and rarely get text alerts, even when everyone knows that school will be canceled. school has been canceled the night before and the app says there is only a 60% chance of a cancellation.
It works, but I hope it updates to material design eventually.
Only some features work. The radar isn't compatible with my Google pixel 2.
It sucks
Outdated
This is abandonware now so don't waste your money on it.

The information is generally pretty accurate, but the website is much better. I don't know what device the screenshots were taken on, but they look much better than they do on my OnePlus 5.  The font is so small I can't read it and the buttons are so small they're nearly un-useable.
Very accurate but needs updating; doesn't work well on my Nexus 5X. Font is also very small and hard to read.
It's so small, i can't read it. Paid the 99 cents for the extra day; regret it. I've tried emailing the owner of the app with no response. Ungrateful losers.

I used to use the website which was slow but worked. Recently the website stopped working so i spent my money on the app, little did I know the app doesn't work either. Don't waste your money and just use another calculator.
Instant uninstall. It doesn't work on a galaxy s6.
The Web version is great. This app is not. You can't see the results. Everything is so small on the screen. Fix it and I'll reinstall
I've used this tool for 5 years and it's only been wrong 3 times
everything extremely tiny.  I can expand it to "very small" if I click on the zip code box to type my zip code in. otherwise, completely unusable.
Only shows half of the screen vertically. I bought this app when I had the S4 in '14 and it worked perfectly. Now I have the S6 and it only displays the left half of the screen.
Zip code and opens number keyboard. Plz help
Awsome
This app doesn't work
The app won't work...just keeps spinning and says it is experiencing difficulties.
The app told me there wasn't going to be a snow day and there wasn't. Then again it is mid August.
Every time I try to check it the website is always down and zip code can't be found.
I was skeptic of all these bad reviews so I bought it.  It works just fine! Put in the zip code and it shows the results.
It doesnt ruin the app

Only works on phones with small screen sizes.  The display doesn't scale so it is totally unreadable on my Nexus 5 (with a 1080x1920 screen).   Works ok on a Nexus S (480x800 screen).   Developer didn't even make use of the most basic android scaling capabilities.  It does generate a snow day probability, however given the poor attention to detail demonstrated by the display it would seem unlikely that much effort has been put into making an accurate prediction.
Doesn't even work!
App doesn't work. Over enlarged, can't access all the info
Not Functional
Love the online version! Wish this worked!
Cannot see preiction
I use it all the time!  I would like the ability to tweet the predictions

Seems to work fine on my Galaxy Note II. Has all the features of the online Das Automatic Snow Day Calculator Online. My only issue that it doesn't seem android friendly...it looks almost like a direct port from iOS to android. Besides that, it works like a charm.
Does not work on my HTC Merge. Email inquiring why has been unanswered after 6 days.
